<h1>Problem 2084 - 2025 Israel 3rd Round, P4 of 4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>A set \(X\) of integers is called \(\textbf{crazy}\) if for all positive integers \(d\) there exists a polynomial \(P \in \mathbb{Z}[x]\) such that \(\deg(P) \geq d\) and for all \(n \in X\) there is some integer \(m\) which satisfies \(P(m)=n\). Are there any infinite crazy sets?</p>
